    "name": "ERP",
    "description": "# Employee Management API - Postman Collection\n**Capstone Project Documentation**\nThis document describes the complete Postman collection used to test the Employee Management REST API.\n- **Base URL**: `http://localhost:8080`\n- **Authentication**: \n  - **GET** endpoints → Public (no authentication required)\n  - **POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE** → Basic Auth  \n    Username: `admin`  \n    Password: `admin123`\n---\n## Employee Endpoints\n### 1. Create Employee (POST)\n**Endpoint**: `POST {{base_url}}/api/employees`\n**Request Body** (JSON):\n```json\n{\n  \"firstName\": \"Ade\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Balogun\",\n  \"email\": \"ade.balogun@company.com\",\n  \"phoneNumber\": \"08012345678\",\n  \"position\": \"Software Engineer\",\n  \"salary\": 850000.00,\n  \"hireDate\": \"2025-03-01\",\n  \"departmentId\": 1\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Expected Status**: `201 Created`\n\n---\n\n### 2\\. List All Employees (GET) - with Pagination & Sorting\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET {{base_url}}/api/employees?page=0&size=10&sort=firstName,asc`\n\n**Query Parameters**:\n\n- `page` → Page number (0-based)\n    \n- `size` → Page size\n    \n- `sort` → Sorting field and direction (e.g., `firstName,asc` or `salary,desc`)\n    \n\n**Expected Status**: `200 OK`\n\n---\n\n### 3\\. Filter Employees by Department (GET)\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET {{base_url}}/api/employees?dept=1&page=0&size=5`\n\n**Query Parameters**:\n\n- `dept` → Department ID (bonus feature)\n    \n- `page` & `size` → Pagination\n    \n\n**Expected Status**: `200 OK`\n\n---\n\n### 4\\. Get Employee by ID (GET)\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET {{base_url}}/api/employees/{id}`\n\nExample: `GET {{base_url}}/api/employees/1`\n\n**Expected Status**: `200 OK` or `404 Not Found`\n\n---\n\n### 5\\. Update Employee - Full Update (PUT)\n\n**Endpoint**: `PUT {{base_url}}/api/employees/{id}`\n\n**Request Body** (JSON):\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"firstName\": \"Adeolu\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Balogun\",\n  \"email\": \"adeolu.b@company.com\",\n  \"phoneNumber\": \"08012345678\",\n  \"position\": \"Senior Software Engineer\",\n  \"salary\": 950000.00,\n  \"hireDate\": \"2025-03-01\",\n  \"departmentId\": 1\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Expected Status**: `200 OK`\n\n---\n\n### 6\\. Partial Update (PATCH)\n\n**Endpoint**: `PATCH {{base_url}}/api/employees/{id}`\n\n**Request Body** (JSON - only fields to update):\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"position\": \"Lead Software Engineer\",\n  \"salary\": 1050000.00\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Expected Status**: `200 OK`\n\n---\n\n### 7\\. Delete Employee (DELETE)\n\n**Endpoint**: `DELETE {{base_url}}/api/employees/{id}`\n\nExample: `DELETE {{base_url}}/api/employees/1`\n\n**Expected Status**: `204 No Content`\n\nJust let me know how you'd like to enhance it!",
